00:09:58,064 --> 00:10:01,467
and we'll also decide
who'll fight for which order.

242
00:10:01,534 --> 00:10:02,935
What's the first order?

243
00:10:03,769 --> 00:10:08,007
-Fridge Game: At this rate, it'll all rot!
-It'll all rot!

244
00:10:08,074 --> 00:10:10,409
-It'll all rot?
-It'll all rot!

245
00:10:10,476 --> 00:10:13,346
It's that line, "We'll all die!"

246
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:15,014
-What is this about?
-I had

247
00:10:15,081 --> 00:10:18,884
-too much of one type of food piled up.
-I see.

248
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:21,988
The point of that order was
cleaning out my fridge.

249
00:10:22,054 --> 00:10:24,023
Cleaning out his fridge.

250
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:27,727
When we open up his fridge,
we'll see some ingredients that he likes,

251
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:29,428
-but there's just too much.
-There's too much.

252
00:10:29,495 --> 00:10:31,797
At this rate, they'll all go bad.

253
00:10:31,864 --> 00:10:34,033
You've come to the right place.

254
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:36,769
-So please use them up and make it good.
-Yes.

255
00:10:36,836 --> 00:10:39,472
Here's the second order. What is it?

256
00:10:39,538 --> 00:10:41,974
-Italian without leftovers.
-Italian without leftovers?

257
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:43,342
-Leftovers?
-Italian without leftovers?

258
00:10:43,409 --> 00:10:46,178
I love Chinese cuisine and Korean cuisine,

259
00:10:46,245 --> 00:10:47,980
-as well as Italian cuisine.
-Yes.

260
00:10:48,047 --> 00:10:49,649
But I haven't been captivated by it

261
00:10:49,715 --> 00:10:53,219
-as much as Chinese or Korean cuisine.
-By Italian cuisine.

262
00:10:53,285 --> 00:10:55,154
-The first bite is great, right?
-Yes.

263
00:10:55,221 --> 00:10:56,922
But it gets cold too quickly,

264
00:10:56,989 --> 00:11:00,726
and it makes me feel a bit sick too.

265
00:11:00,793 --> 00:11:03,162
So you never enjoyed it deliciously
until the last bite.

266
00:11:03,229 --> 00:11:05,564
I don't think
I've ever had such an Italian dish.

267
00:11:05,631 --> 00:11:07,833
So I want to experience that today.

268
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:11,604
-You must choose one of the two.
-One of the two.

269
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,239
Sam raises his hand first.

270
00:11:13,305 --> 00:11:16,242
-I'll cook the Italian cuisine.
-Of course.

271
00:11:16,308 --> 00:11:18,210
-I've been looking forward to it.
-Have you?

272
00:11:18,277 --> 00:11:21,514
-It's for his same-aged friend.
-Thank you.

273
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:24,350
-And?
-And we have three chefs left.

274
00:11:24,417 --> 00:11:27,353
Choi Hyun-suk, Choi Kang-rok,
and Kim Sohyi, three chefs.

275
00:11:27,420 --> 00:11:28,454
I will make

276
00:11:29,221 --> 00:11:30,956
Italian cuisine.

277
00:11:31,023 --> 00:11:32,725
Against Sam?

278
00:11:32,792 --> 00:11:34,427
-I'm also an Italian chef…
-I see.

279
00:11:34,493 --> 00:11:36,162
…and I have that competitive spirit.

280
00:11:36,228 --> 00:11:38,497
He said he was Sam's fan,

281
00:11:38,564 --> 00:11:40,766
but I'll turn him into my fan.

282
00:11:42,468 --> 00:11:44,170
ITALIAN WITHOUT LEFTOVERS
SAM KIM VS CHOI HYUN-SUK

283
00:11:44,236 --> 00:11:45,471
-It's a big match.
-That confidence.

284
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:48,040
-I will make Italian cuisine.
-Against Sam?

285
00:11:48,107 --> 00:11:50,276
-I'm also an Italian chef…
-I see.

286
00:11:50,342 --> 00:11:52,645
…and I have that competitive spirit.

287
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:55,147
-So it's you and her?
-He said he was Sam's fan…

288
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:57,116
There are only two spots left.

289
00:11:57,183 --> 00:12:00,019
-You're all awful.
-We should've been more considerate.

290
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:01,320
What are the chances?

291
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:03,589
Remember how Sam raised his hand
right away?

292
00:12:03,656 --> 00:12:05,591
-Automatically.
-He was put there automatically.

293
00:12:05,658 --> 00:12:09,795
-The judge versus the winner.
-This is really like <i>Squid Game</i>.

294
00:12:09,862 --> 00:12:11,964
-It's a real <i>Squid Game</i>.
-Kim Sohyi versus Choi Kang-rok.

295
00:12:12,031 --> 00:12:14,100
This is totally cheating.

296
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:17,169
It's so cruel.

297
00:12:17,236 --> 00:12:19,805
We don't even know what's in his fridge.

298
00:12:19,872 --> 00:12:21,874
The ingredients are irrelevant.

299
00:12:21,941 --> 00:12:23,843
I'm going to win no matter what.

300
00:12:23,909 --> 00:12:25,778
It makes no sense for me to fight him.

301
00:12:25,845 --> 00:12:28,748
-Because you'll win anyway.
-You'll win.

302
00:12:28,814 --> 00:12:30,883
Are you going to just sit there?

303
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,786
Yes, well. You're right.

304
00:12:33,853 --> 00:12:35,421
What are you saying?

305
00:12:35,488 --> 00:12:37,757
-You must have a resolution.
-Yes, I wonder.

306
00:12:37,823 --> 00:12:38,824
Right?

307
00:12:38,891 --> 00:12:40,860
You better talk right. I'll kill you.

308
00:12:40,926 --> 00:12:42,194
Can you please interpret?

309
00:12:42,261 --> 00:12:43,562
"You better talk right. I'll kill you."

310
00:12:44,663 --> 00:12:47,533
-That's not an interpretation.
-Give us an interpretation.

311
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,970
If you don't talk properly, you'll die.

312
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:53,906
-That was it.
-Thank you.

313
00:12:53,973 --> 00:12:55,775
First of all,

314
00:12:55,841 --> 00:12:57,543
that order

315
00:12:58,210 --> 00:13:00,045
does not sound too hard.

316
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:02,214
Hey, that confidence.

317
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:03,916
-I'll try my best.
-You will.

318
00:13:03,983 --> 00:13:05,217
He's got nerves.

319
00:13:07,052 --> 00:13:08,988
-He's a fool rushing in.
-Foie gras.

320
00:13:09,054 --> 00:13:11,056
I chose him back then

321
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:13,459
because I thought he did things right.

322
00:13:13,526 --> 00:13:17,797
But I didn't expect him
to stand before me as my enemy.

323
00:13:17,863 --> 00:13:19,899
THE MATCH TO LOOK FORWARD TO,
TEACHER VS PUPIL

324
00:13:19,965 --> 00:13:21,066
It'll rake in a million views.

325
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:26,172
It's time to turn
Sung-tae's fridge inside out.

326
00:13:26,238 --> 00:13:27,640
It's this fridge right here.

327
00:13:27,706 --> 00:13:30,776
-Yes.
-It surely looks like it belongs at home.

328
00:13:30,843 --> 00:13:32,745
Yes, my heart is beating so fast.

329
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:34,113
I don't know what's inside.

330
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:36,549
-I see.
-It's probably everything you know.

331
00:13:36,615 --> 00:13:38,751
I'm afraid I'll see
things like chicken bones.

332
00:13:40,386 --> 00:13:42,655
PREVIOUSLY, J-HOPE'S FRIDGE

333
00:13:42,721 --> 00:13:44,657
This is just like
something that was in my fridge!

334
00:13:44,723 --> 00:13:46,826
I almost used it to make broth.

335
00:13:46,892 --> 00:13:48,661
-Bone broth.
-What's that doing there?

336
00:13:48,727 --> 00:13:51,831
But people thought it was funny.

337
00:13:51,897 --> 00:13:55,734
-We're all humans.
-He left those after he ate a chicken.

338
00:13:55,801 --> 00:13:57,603
-Shall we? Okay.
-Shall we?

339
00:13:57,670 --> 00:14:00,172
Sung-tae's fridge.

340
00:14:00,239 --> 00:14:01,707
-There are photos.
-There are.

341
00:14:01,774 --> 00:14:04,743
This must be
when he played a police officer.

342
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:09,348
Yes, I did that in <i>Good Boy</i>,
a JTBC drama premiering on May 31st.

343
00:14:09,415 --> 00:14:10,916
Is this from <i>Good Boy</i>?

344
00:14:10,983 --> 00:14:13,519
-That's from <i>Good Boy</i>.
-And the cast.

345
00:14:13,586 --> 00:14:15,087
-Next to this?
-I see.

346
00:14:15,154 --> 00:14:19,358
-Park Bo-gum.
-I see Park Bo-gum.

347
00:14:19,425 --> 00:14:21,627
Park Bo-gum, Lee Sang-yi, Kim So-hyun,

348
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:23,963
-Tae Won-seok, and Heo Sung-tae.
-Oh, my.

349
00:14:24,029 --> 00:14:26,065
-Have you all become close?
-Yes.

350
00:14:26,131 --> 00:14:27,733
They're all so nice.

351
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:30,236
-They approached me first.
-I see.

352
00:14:30,302 --> 00:14:34,073
Can you ask one of them to be here
around when <i>Good Boy</i> goes on air?

353
00:14:34,139 --> 00:14:37,309
-I'll talk to them.
-Please talk to them.

354
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:38,544
Thank you.

355
00:14:38,611 --> 00:14:40,713
-Let's take a look at his fridge.
-Yes.

356
00:14:40,779 --> 00:14:44,083
-Sung-tae looks nervous. A sip of water.
-A sip of water.

357
00:14:44,149 --> 00:14:48,420
It must feel unfamiliar
to present his fridge in front of people.

358
00:14:48,487 --> 00:14:50,756
We present…

359
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:55,761
-Sung-tae's fridge!
-Go!

360
00:14:55,828 --> 00:14:57,363
Whoa, what is this?

361
00:14:57,429 --> 00:14:59,031
-Sung-tae's fridge!
-Go!

362
00:14:59,098 --> 00:15:00,933
Whoa, what is this?

363
00:15:02,534 --> 00:15:04,703
-He has lots of stuff.
-What are those?

364
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:06,872
-It's full.
-It's packed.

365
00:15:06,939 --> 00:15:08,974
I can already tell that you enjoy cooking.

366
00:15:09,541 --> 00:15:12,611
-Yes.
-It's neatly organized.

367
00:15:12,678 --> 00:15:14,446
I see some <i>doenjang </i>on the first shelf.

368
00:15:14,513 --> 00:15:17,283
There are lots of side dishes
on the second shelf.

369
00:15:17,349 --> 00:15:19,385
Let's look at these.

370
00:15:19,451 --> 00:15:21,353
We were surprised at how good

371
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:23,789
-j-hope's mother was at cooking.
-We were.

372
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:26,158
-<i>Kkakdugi</i>.
-<i>Kkakdugi</i>.

373
00:15:26,225 --> 00:15:28,193
This one looks like napa cabbage kimchi.

374
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,361
It's napa cabbage kimchi.

375
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:32,765
-I think this is <i>mukeunji</i>.
-Yes.

376
00:15:32,831 --> 00:15:34,066
Chive kimchi.

377
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:37,770
-Try opening these too. Let's look.
-That's a lot.

378
00:15:37,836 --> 00:15:39,171
This is kimchi too.

379
00:15:39,238 --> 00:15:41,807
All four containers are kimchi.
This one is kimchi too.

380
00:15:41,874 --> 00:15:43,676
I have too much kimchi.

381
00:15:43,742 --> 00:15:45,010
This is kimchi too.

382
00:15:45,077 --> 00:15:47,613
I think kimchi is one of the ingredients
you need to use up.

383
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:50,849
KEY INGREDIENT 3: KIMCHI,
A REQUEST TO USE IT UP

384
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:55,020
I haven't seen that much kimchi
even at a side dish store.

385
00:15:55,087 --> 00:15:58,157
People in Gyeongsang Province
eat lots of kimchi.

386
00:15:58,223 --> 00:16:00,225
Families who have a good cook

387
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:02,428
-always have many types of kimchi.
-Right.

388
00:16:02,494 --> 00:16:06,432
-Lots of veggies in the crisper drawer.
-Yes.

389
00:16:06,498 --> 00:16:09,368
-Cabbage and onion.
-Onion.

390
00:16:09,435 --> 00:16:13,973
-I see oranges, blueberries, and apples.
-Blueberries.

391
00:16:14,039 --> 00:16:16,308
And now, the freezer.

392
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:19,979
My gosh. He must've had <i>tteokguk</i>
on Lunar New Year.

393
00:16:20,045 --> 00:16:21,146
Rice cakes for <i>tteokguk</i>.

394
00:16:21,213 --> 00:16:22,281
Why do you have so much?

395
00:16:22,348 --> 00:16:24,450
There's more.

396
00:16:24,516 --> 00:16:27,219
-Another one.
-Do you like <i>tteokguk</i>?

397
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:28,787
I like that texture.

398
00:16:28,854 --> 00:16:32,524
-The chewy texture.
-I like <i>tteokbokki, tteokguk</i> and <i>sujebi</i>.

399
00:16:33,759 --> 00:16:36,061
Should they also use this up too?

400
00:16:36,128 --> 00:16:38,430
Yes. Why do I have
so much food to use up?

401
00:16:38,497 --> 00:16:41,367
He likes the texture
of rice cake in <i>tteokguk</i>.

402
00:16:41,433 --> 00:16:43,335
Please use lots of these too.

403
00:16:43,402 --> 00:16:45,371
-Is there more?
-There is.

404
00:16:45,437 --> 00:16:48,474
-Hey, natto.
-Natto.

405
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:49,975
I'm seeing lots of natto.

406
00:16:50,042 --> 00:16:51,410
There are lots of natto.

407
00:16:51,477 --> 00:16:54,113
-He has lots of natto.
-He has natto here.

408
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:55,714
I like natto.

409
00:16:55,781 --> 00:16:57,249
You like-o natto?

410
00:16:57,316 --> 00:17:00,552
Try filming all the way inside.

411
00:17:00,619 --> 00:17:03,722
Natto… Whoa! There are stacks of natto.

412
00:17:03,789 --> 00:17:05,791
You must love natto.

413
00:17:05,858 --> 00:17:06,859
I eat two packs a day.

414
00:17:06,925 --> 00:17:09,895
-You eat it all day.
-Is there a particular reason?

415
00:17:09,962 --> 00:17:11,997
I just like that texture.

416
00:17:12,064 --> 00:17:13,932
I see. It's the texture.

417
00:17:13,999 --> 00:17:16,001
-It has that sticky texture.
-Yes.

418
00:17:16,068 --> 00:17:18,303
I found something suspicious in here.

419
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:20,039
-What's this?
-No!

420
00:17:20,105 --> 00:17:21,440
I think that's food waste.

421
00:17:21,507 --> 00:17:22,808
-What? Food waste?
-Food waste?

422
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,376
WAS THAT WHY HE WAS SO ANXIOUS?

423
00:17:24,443 --> 00:17:25,611
It's for our eyes only.

424
00:17:25,677 --> 00:17:28,614
-Gosh, Sung-tae!
-Why?

425
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:32,184
-Gosh, Sung-tae!
-Why?

426
00:17:32,251 --> 00:17:34,353
-Sung-tae!
-Why?

427
00:17:34,420 --> 00:17:35,721
I don't know what that is.

428
00:17:35,788 --> 00:17:37,623
Was it that bad?

429
00:17:37,689 --> 00:17:38,724
WHAT COULD IT BE?

430
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:41,093
This was <i>tteokbokki</i>
with beef loin topping.

431
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:42,728
-I see.
-<i>Tteokbokki </i>with beef loin topping.

432
00:17:42,795 --> 00:17:45,864
-It wasn't food waste.
-This isn't mold. It's ice.

433
00:17:45,931 --> 00:17:48,867
-It's just frozen.
-It was just frost.

434
00:17:48,934 --> 00:17:52,337
It's such a shame, though.
You didn't even mix it.

435
00:17:52,404 --> 00:17:53,906
-Yes, it went straight inside.
-It's too old.

436
00:17:53,972 --> 00:17:56,875
-We found at least one thing like this.
-Yes.

437
00:17:56,942 --> 00:17:57,943
Hey.

438
00:17:58,510 --> 00:18:00,612
-Marsh clam soup.
-This looks so good.

439
00:18:00,679 --> 00:18:03,515
-It's a product that makes it easy to eat.
-Yes.

440
00:18:03,582 --> 00:18:04,817
When do you eat this?

441
00:18:04,883 --> 00:18:09,555
I eat it as breakfast when I crave it
by boiling it in a pot.

442
00:18:09,621 --> 00:18:10,956
You boil it in a pot.

443
00:18:11,023 --> 00:18:12,991
And what's next?

444
00:18:13,058 --> 00:18:14,993
Why do you have so many chicken breasts?

445
00:18:15,060 --> 00:18:17,830
There are like 30 of these.

446
00:18:18,530 --> 00:18:21,433
KEY INGREDIENT 9: CHICKEN BREAST,
A REQUEST TO USE IT UP

447
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,969
I bought those

448
00:18:24,036 --> 00:18:28,707
when I began to shoot <i>Good Boy</i>,
the JTBC drama,

449
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:30,109
because I had to play a wrestler.

450
00:18:30,175 --> 00:18:33,645
It's the story of national athletes
who have won medals

451
00:18:33,712 --> 00:18:35,380
that become police officers
to fight evil.

452
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:38,450
-You had to be a bit bigger.
-You had to be in shape.

453
00:18:38,517 --> 00:18:41,553
But we filmed that scene
much faster than I expected,

454
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:43,856
leaving me with so many chicken breasts.

455
00:18:43,922 --> 00:18:45,190
I have to use those up too.

456
00:18:45,257 --> 00:18:47,693
-You have to use this up too.
-These need to go too.

457
00:18:47,759 --> 00:18:49,728
-What's this over here?
-Tomato sauce.

458
00:18:49,795 --> 00:18:51,396
-It's tomato sauce.
-Tomato sauce.

459
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:55,000
There are ingredients
you can use for Italian dishes.

460
00:18:55,067 --> 00:18:58,303
I bought those and tried making pasta.

461
00:18:58,370 --> 00:19:01,840
Olive oil, and two bottles.

462
00:19:01,907 --> 00:19:05,244
-He has spaghetti too.
-He does. Okay.

463
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:07,779
That was all for Sung-tae's fridge.

464
00:19:07,846 --> 00:19:10,782
HOW WILL THESE MATCHES UNFOLD?

465
00:19:10,849 --> 00:19:15,087
The first cook-off
with Sung-tae's ingredients

466
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:18,056
is held between Chef Choi Kang-rok,
aka Mr. Slow

467
00:19:18,123 --> 00:19:21,660
and Chef Kim Sohyi, aka Ms. Do-It-Right.

468
00:19:21,727 --> 00:19:26,098
This huge match takes place
twelve whole years

469
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:27,633
-after their initial encounter.
-Whoa.

470
00:19:27,699 --> 00:19:32,337
They have met here on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
for a 15-minute cook-off.

471
00:19:32,404 --> 00:19:34,072
-Yes.
-I can't believe I'm seeing this.

472
00:19:34,139 --> 00:19:36,408
We're looking forward to this round.

473
00:19:36,475 --> 00:19:37,910
The judge versus the contestant.

474
00:19:37,976 --> 00:19:39,411
This will rake in a million views.

475
00:19:40,145 --> 00:19:42,915
Would you like to participate
in the Fridge Game?

476
00:19:43,815 --> 00:19:46,685
Welcome. It's your first time
on<i> Chef & My Fridge</i>, right?

477
00:19:47,252 --> 00:19:48,820
ROK HAS PLAYED THIS GAME BEFORE

478
00:19:48,887 --> 00:19:51,256
Hello, it's your first time
on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>, right?

479
00:19:51,323 --> 00:19:53,292
-Do it right.
-"Do it right."

480
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:55,928
I'll end up losing face if you lose. Okay?

481
00:19:56,595 --> 00:19:58,230
SHAKING IN FEAR

482
00:19:58,297 --> 00:19:59,965
He was the winner she chose,

483
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:02,801
so she wouldn't want him
to go down too easily.

484
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:05,804
-She must be conflicted.
-You're right.

485
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:07,272
We should be neck and neck

486
00:20:07,339 --> 00:20:10,075
-to make me go, "I chose the right one."
-Yes.

487
00:20:10,142 --> 00:20:11,843
Do it right, okay?

488
00:20:11,910 --> 00:20:13,845
I will do it right.

489
00:20:13,912 --> 00:20:18,517
Are you okay with us doing
a final check with five minutes remaining?

490
00:20:18,584 --> 00:20:20,018
You must be tired enough, so stay.

491
00:20:20,085 --> 00:20:22,554
Why are you trying to steal my job?

492
00:20:22,621 --> 00:20:25,023
-I'm the expert at tasting food.
-Yes.

493
00:20:25,090 --> 00:20:26,992
If you want to taste it, you can ask.

494
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:29,161
Then I'll go over and taste his food.

495
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:30,229
That confidence.

496
00:20:30,295 --> 00:20:31,997
So you'll taste his food too?

497
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:34,466
Of course. That's my work habit.

498
00:20:34,533 --> 00:20:37,569
-Will that be possible?
-Chef Kang-rok

499
00:20:37,636 --> 00:20:40,639
is staring into the void once again.

500
00:20:40,706 --> 00:20:42,507
What's on your mind?

501
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:44,776
She won't have time to taste my food.

502
00:20:46,178 --> 00:20:48,247
-Hey. I knew it.
-I knew it.

503
00:20:48,313 --> 00:20:51,750
That's something you can say as someone
who has done the 15-minute cook-offs.

504
00:20:51,817 --> 00:20:54,620
Yes, he's become rather bold now.
He's got nerves.

505
00:20:54,686 --> 00:20:56,688
-"He's got nerves."
-Yes.

506
00:20:56,755 --> 00:20:59,258
It'll be amazing
if she actually tastes his food.

507
00:20:59,324 --> 00:21:01,560
She won't have the time to do that.

508
00:21:01,627 --> 00:21:03,362
-"She won't have the time."
-Yes.

509
00:21:03,428 --> 00:21:07,299
You came from Vienna, Austria.
Aren't you feeling tired?

510
00:21:07,366 --> 00:21:09,668
He seems <i>moljjang</i>, so I'm fine.

511
00:21:10,235 --> 00:21:12,104
Did you understand
what I meant by <i>moljjang</i>?

512
00:21:12,170 --> 00:21:13,472
<i>Moljjang</i>?

513
00:21:13,538 --> 00:21:15,841
-Fine?
-Intact?

514
00:21:15,907 --> 00:21:18,944
Can you interpret this? He looks <i>moljjang</i>.

515
00:21:19,011 --> 00:21:21,146
WHAT DOES MOLJJANG MEAN?

516
00:21:22,014 --> 00:21:23,248
I don't know what that means.

517
00:21:24,716 --> 00:21:28,120
-You are supposed to interpret her!
-What's going on?

518
00:21:28,186 --> 00:21:30,922
-<i>Moljjang</i>?
-<i>Moljjang</i>.

519
00:21:30,989 --> 00:21:32,291
He looks <i>moljjang</i>.

520
00:21:32,357 --> 00:21:34,826
-We'll see it in the caption.
-Was that German?

521
00:21:34,893 --> 00:21:36,995
IT MEANS KANG-ROK
LOOKS EASY TO DEAL WITH

522
00:21:37,062 --> 00:21:40,699
We provide a perk
to all chefs who come for the first time.

523
00:21:40,766 --> 00:21:42,868
-Yes, right.
-Right.

524
00:21:42,934 --> 00:21:44,436
-Here are the perks.
-Okay.

525
00:21:44,503 --> 00:21:46,271
You can start a minute earlier.

526
00:21:46,338 --> 00:21:49,541
You can stop your opponent for a minute
during the 15 minutes.

527
00:21:49,608 --> 00:21:52,344
Lastly, you can invoke UNICHEF
for a minute.

528
00:21:52,411 --> 00:21:55,547
-"You can go cut this."
-You can get help for a minute.

529
00:21:55,614 --> 00:21:58,216
I'm the oldest one here,

530
00:21:58,283 --> 00:21:59,451
so I'll use all three.

531
00:21:59,518 --> 00:22:01,286
I'LL USE ALL THREE

532
00:22:01,353 --> 00:22:04,256
-I went on a flight to be here.
-Wait.

533
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:05,957
You're up against Kang-rok.

534
00:22:06,024 --> 00:22:08,694
I can't lose. I have to win.

535
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:10,796
-I've never seen you like this.
-Same.

536
00:22:10,862 --> 00:22:12,364
-"No way."
-I need to be honest.

537
00:22:12,431 --> 00:22:13,699
-I need to be honest.
-My gosh.

538
00:22:13,765 --> 00:22:15,300
I thought she might not use it.

539
00:22:15,367 --> 00:22:17,169
I'm sorry, but you must choose one.

540
00:22:17,235 --> 00:22:20,906
-Then, the last one. UNICHEF? That one.
-UNICHEF?

541
00:22:20,972 --> 00:22:22,574
-Is that the best?
-UNICHEF for a minute.

542
00:22:22,641 --> 00:22:26,311
Chef Kang-rok looks dumbfounded right now.

543
00:22:26,378 --> 00:22:29,748
-No, I'm about to cry.
-You're about to cry?

544
00:22:29,815 --> 00:22:31,950
He didn't think she'd be this harsh.

545
00:22:32,017 --> 00:22:34,820
People can be cold
when it comes to a competition.

546
00:22:35,654 --> 00:22:36,655
CHEF KANG-ROK:

547
00:22:36,722 --> 00:22:38,824
SPAGHETTI, CHICKEN BREAST, NATTO,
KIMCHI, TUNA SAUCE, LAVER FLAKES

548
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:42,094
Chef Kang-rok,
what's the dish you prepared?

549
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:44,930
If he wants a recipe
to use up these ingredients,

550
00:22:44,996 --> 00:22:47,099
it cannot be too hard,

551
00:22:47,165 --> 00:22:49,101
it needs to use lots of ingredients,

552
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:51,036
and it needs to be completed

553
00:22:51,103 --> 00:22:52,838
even if you ignore
the order of the recipe.

554
00:22:52,904 --> 00:22:55,307
-Yes.
-Yet it has to taste good.

555
00:22:56,174 --> 00:22:57,175
That's what I prepared.

556
00:22:57,809 --> 00:22:59,378
THAT'S ALL?

557
00:22:59,444 --> 00:23:01,813
So what's the dish you're making?

558
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,415
Leave Me Natto-lone.

559
00:23:03,482 --> 00:23:05,083
-Leave Me Natto-lone.
-Leave Me Natto-lone.

560
00:23:05,150 --> 00:23:08,120
-That's what it's called.
-He'll use natto.

561
00:23:08,186 --> 00:23:09,955
-Leave Me Natto-lone.
-Leave Me Natto-lone.

562
00:23:10,021 --> 00:23:12,224
It means you'll use natto

563
00:23:12,290 --> 00:23:16,194
-and he's saying that to Chef Sohyi.
-Yes, he wanted me to hear that.

564
00:23:16,261 --> 00:23:17,996
What's the recipe?

565
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:21,333
Natto and kimchi go well together.

566
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:23,068
-They were both fermented.
-Yes.

567
00:23:23,135 --> 00:23:26,705
-And so are natto and dried laver.
-They are.

568
00:23:26,772 --> 00:23:29,975
-Laver and kimchi.
-Like laver wraps with kimchi and natto?

569
00:23:30,041 --> 00:23:32,411
This recipe will help him use up natto

570
00:23:32,477 --> 00:23:35,580
like he's slurping on it.

571
00:23:35,647 --> 00:23:38,049
Slurping? That must mean noodles.

572
00:23:38,116 --> 00:23:40,352
I'm going to make pasta with natto.

573
00:23:41,386 --> 00:23:42,988
-Natto pasta.
-Natto pasta.

574
00:23:43,822 --> 00:23:45,424
CHEF SOHYI: PERILLA LEAVES,
RICE CAKE, PERILLA OIL, SHRIMPS

575
00:23:45,490 --> 00:23:46,992
CABBAGE, RADISH, KIMCHI, DOENJANG,
BROTH PACK, DRIED LAVER FLAKES

576
00:23:47,058 --> 00:23:49,661
Chef Sohyi, what's your dish?

577
00:23:49,728 --> 00:23:52,164
It's called Master <i>Tteokguk</i> Korea.

578
00:23:52,230 --> 00:23:54,599
-Master <i>Tteokguk </i>Korea. MTK.
-I see.

579
00:23:54,666 --> 00:23:57,669
-It's MTK.
-It's MTK, not MCK.

580
00:23:57,736 --> 00:23:59,771
-It's MTK, not MCK.
-MTK, not MCK.

581
00:23:59,838 --> 00:24:02,240
How is it different from regular <i>tteokguk</i>?

582
00:24:02,307 --> 00:24:06,478
I'll add radish to <i>tteokguk</i>.

583
00:24:06,545 --> 00:24:07,913
-Radish in <i>tteokguk</i>?
-Yes.

584
00:24:07,979 --> 00:24:10,549
I am originally from Busan,

585
00:24:10,615 --> 00:24:13,518
so this was something
my mother used to make for me.

586
00:24:13,585 --> 00:24:16,288
-It's what I want to eat. I like kimchi.
-Kimchi.

587
00:24:16,354 --> 00:24:17,823
And <i>doenjang </i>too.

588
00:24:17,889 --> 00:24:22,160
It's a kind of <i>tteokguk</i>
where I throw in everything I want to eat.

589
00:24:22,227 --> 00:24:23,895
Please use some chicken breast too.

590
00:24:23,962 --> 00:24:26,431
Will any of you use chicken breast?

591
00:24:26,498 --> 00:24:28,934
I'll use chicken breast.

592
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,069
-I see.
-He'll use it.

593
00:24:31,136 --> 00:24:33,805
He'll use up natto and chicken breast.

594
00:24:33,872 --> 00:24:36,341
Just as she said,

595
00:24:36,408 --> 00:24:39,945
I also like to pour in
everything I like when I cook.

596
00:24:40,011 --> 00:24:41,413
I'm looking forward to the <i>tteokguk</i>.

597
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:44,583
-He looks forward to the <i>tteokguk</i>.
-She has a similar style.

598
00:24:44,649 --> 00:24:47,953
-But I did all the explaining.
-The natto…

599
00:24:48,019 --> 00:24:51,823
Chef Rok wanted to make an appeal
while looking at me.

600
00:24:51,890 --> 00:24:54,359
-Just tell them what you want to.
-What's wrong?

601
00:24:54,426 --> 00:24:55,627
Well.

602
00:24:55,694 --> 00:24:58,230
I was the one who said
I'd put everything in.

603
00:24:58,296 --> 00:24:59,431
So why <i>tteokguk</i>?

604
00:24:59,998 --> 00:25:01,766
YELLING

605
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:03,301
He's right.

606
00:25:03,368 --> 00:25:05,036
He snapped.

607
00:25:05,103 --> 00:25:06,671
"So why <i>tteokguk</i>?"

608
00:25:07,572 --> 00:25:10,876
I don't think you're in a position
to be judged by anyone,

609
00:25:10,942 --> 00:25:15,146
but you will be judged
by Judge Heo Sung-tae today.

610
00:25:15,213 --> 00:25:17,516
Do you want to say anything
to the fridge owner?

611
00:25:19,184 --> 00:25:20,418
I'm in your hands.

612
00:25:20,986 --> 00:25:23,755
SHE'S HERE AS A CONTESTANT TODAY

613
00:25:23,822 --> 00:25:26,358
-I'm in your hands.
-Yes, that's how she feels.

614
00:25:26,424 --> 00:25:32,797
And now, let us begin the round
with Sung-tae's ingredients.

615
00:25:32,864 --> 00:25:35,734
She was the one
who made Kang-rok who he is today.

616
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:39,804
She plans to do things right
to show the class of a judge.

617
00:25:39,871 --> 00:25:42,140
Chef Kim Sohyi is in this battle.

618
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:44,342
He says he was the first
on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

619
00:25:44,409 --> 00:25:48,547
He wants to forget the credentials
and fight the judge today.

620
00:25:48,613 --> 00:25:50,715
Chef Choi Kang-rok is up against her.

621
00:25:50,782 --> 00:25:53,752
The two face each other as enemies
after 12 years.

622
00:25:53,818 --> 00:25:56,388
Who'll win this round?

623
00:25:56,454 --> 00:26:01,726
-Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!
-Begin!

624
00:26:04,462 --> 00:26:06,665
-Let's do this.
-I wonder how he feels.

625
00:26:06,731 --> 00:26:08,967
I wonder how he feels.

626
00:26:09,034 --> 00:26:12,070
They've come to this fateful moment
to fight against each other,

627
00:26:12,137 --> 00:26:14,239
the judge versus the winning contestant.

628
00:26:14,306 --> 00:26:16,875
-It must feel so odd for them.
-Yes.

629
00:26:17,542 --> 00:26:20,579
1. PUT BROTH PACK INTO
BOILING WATER AND MAKE BROTH

630
00:26:21,146 --> 00:26:22,881
AN INGREDIENT TO USE UP:
RICE CAKE

631
00:26:22,948 --> 00:26:24,716
She must be boiling rice cake separately.

632
00:26:24,783 --> 00:26:26,918
Are you boiling rice cake
in two separate pots?

633
00:26:26,985 --> 00:26:28,954
No, I'm making broth in one of these.

634
00:26:29,020 --> 00:26:30,622
-That's broth, that's rice cake.
-Yes.

635
00:26:30,689 --> 00:26:33,158
She's boiling the two separately.

636
00:26:33,224 --> 00:26:35,660
Otherwise, it'll feel too dry.

637
00:26:35,727 --> 00:26:36,928
The soup will be too thick.

638
00:26:36,995 --> 00:26:40,298
I was the most worried
because thin rice cakes cook quickly.

639
00:26:40,365 --> 00:26:43,368
She put those in too early,
so I wonder how she'll use those.

640
00:26:44,469 --> 00:26:46,972
KIM SOHYI BEGINS
TO COOK IN FULL SWING

641
00:26:47,539 --> 00:26:50,308
SHE PUTS THE GLOVES ON FIRST

642
00:26:51,009 --> 00:26:54,679
I think Chef Sohyi will taste his food
later on. She looks relaxed.

643
00:26:54,746 --> 00:26:55,880
I feel more nervous.

644
00:26:55,947 --> 00:26:57,349
-Wait, the time.
-She looks so carefree.

645
00:26:57,415 --> 00:26:58,416
You don't have much time.

646
00:26:58,483 --> 00:27:01,519
-Aren't you too relaxed?
-You're too relaxed.

647
00:27:01,586 --> 00:27:03,421
She's using radish.

648
00:27:03,488 --> 00:27:05,256
What's she doing by turning it around?

649
00:27:05,323 --> 00:27:07,492
I've never seen anyone
peel it by siding the blade up.

650
00:27:07,559 --> 00:27:10,295
-Yes, what is that?
-Whoa.

651
00:27:10,362 --> 00:27:12,664
She's scraping the outside.

652
00:27:12,731 --> 00:27:15,266
I think she's getting rid
of the excess parts.

653
00:27:16,735 --> 00:27:17,836
-Yes.
-I've never seen that before.

654
00:27:17,902 --> 00:27:19,037
She's doing that too.

655
00:27:20,205 --> 00:27:22,107
3. SCRAPE THE RADISH SKIN,

656
00:27:22,173 --> 00:27:24,242
CUT INTO BIG PIECES,
AND BOIL IN BROTH

657
00:27:24,809 --> 00:27:28,279
SHE FINALLY BEGINS
TO JULIENNE THEM

658
00:27:29,014 --> 00:27:30,115
CUTTING IMMACULATELY

659
00:27:30,181 --> 00:27:33,018
Look at how Chef Sohyi
juliennes the radish. That's so cool.

660
00:27:33,852 --> 00:27:36,588
She's the Korean cuisine expert.

661
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:37,889
THE QUEEN OF KOREAN CUISINE

662
00:27:37,956 --> 00:27:40,725
She's going to boil the radish
by julienning them.

663
00:27:40,792 --> 00:27:43,595
Then it'll cook much faster.

664
00:27:44,596 --> 00:27:47,766
HER STUDENT, CHOI KANG-ROK,
BEGINS WITH GREEN ONION

665
00:27:48,566 --> 00:27:50,335
HE TURNS THE GREEN ONION AROUND
AND MAKES CUTS

666
00:27:50,402 --> 00:27:52,804
-They're both cutting.
-He's making cuts.

667
00:27:52,871 --> 00:27:57,275
It looks like he's making cuts
to that piece of green onion.

668
00:27:57,842 --> 00:27:59,978
HE BEGINS TO CUT

669
00:28:00,845 --> 00:28:03,615
HE BECAME MUCH FASTER

670
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:07,118
IT'S ME, THE WINNER

671
00:28:07,686 --> 00:28:11,423
BRAND NEW CHOI KANG-ROK

672
00:28:11,990 --> 00:28:14,292
THE WINNER PULLS OUT
DRIED LAVER FLAKES

673
00:28:15,193 --> 00:28:17,429
Whoa.

674
00:28:18,663 --> 00:28:21,299
KANG-ROK IS STILL THE SAME

675
00:28:21,366 --> 00:28:23,001
Hmm?

676
00:28:25,570 --> 00:28:27,172
TROUBLE WITH THE STOVE
EVEN AFTER THREE MONTHS

677
00:28:27,739 --> 00:28:29,507
HE FINALLY SUCCEEDS

678
00:28:30,141 --> 00:28:31,576
1. PUT LAVER, CRUSHED GARLIC,
TUNA SAUCE

679
00:28:31,643 --> 00:28:32,944
INTO BOILING WATER
TO MAKE LAVER SOUP

680
00:28:33,011 --> 00:28:34,112
What's Chef Kang-rok doing?

681
00:28:34,179 --> 00:28:37,015
-Did he use dried laver?
-I'm soaking dried laver.

682
00:28:37,082 --> 00:28:38,349
I'm making laver soup.

683
00:28:38,416 --> 00:28:41,286
-I see. Laver soup.
-He's making soup.

684
00:28:41,352 --> 00:28:43,621
-And he gets the pasta.
-How is this…

685
00:28:45,123 --> 00:28:47,392
-"How many minutes?"
-It's…

686
00:28:47,459 --> 00:28:49,127
-What's that? Spaghetti?
-Yes.

687
00:28:49,194 --> 00:28:51,229
Eight to nine minutes.

688
00:28:52,063 --> 00:28:55,133
Will the winner surpass the judge?

689
00:28:56,501 --> 00:28:58,536
SHE CHECKS
THE RICE CAKE IN WATER

690
00:28:58,603 --> 00:29:00,472
The rice cake will cook quickly.

691
00:29:00,538 --> 00:29:03,775
It may end up overcooked. Is that okay?

692
00:29:04,642 --> 00:29:05,777
SHE PUTS THE BROTH
INTO THE RICE CAKE POT

693
00:29:05,844 --> 00:29:09,714
-The broth.
-She puts the broth into that pot.

694
00:29:11,549 --> 00:29:13,051
It's boiling over.

695
00:29:13,118 --> 00:29:14,519
-It's boiling over.
-It's boiling over.

696
00:29:14,586 --> 00:29:17,756
-It's boiling over.
-You have to blow on it.

697
00:29:17,822 --> 00:29:20,091
-Is it boiling over?
-Which stove is it?

698
00:29:20,658 --> 00:29:22,861
AT THIS RATE,
IT'LL ALL BOIL OVER

699
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:25,063
Which stove is it?

700
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:28,032
It's boiling over.

701
00:29:28,099 --> 00:29:29,334
She's not used to the stove.

702
00:29:29,400 --> 00:29:32,170
-Gosh.
-Did the heat turn off?

703
00:29:32,237 --> 00:29:35,140
-She's…
-She pours it into the pot.

704
00:29:35,206 --> 00:29:38,777
The one in the front is
this one and this one.

705
00:29:38,843 --> 00:29:40,512
There's a little diagram.

706
00:29:40,578 --> 00:29:41,746
She can't figure out the stove.

707
00:29:41,813 --> 00:29:43,248
She should've checked it first.

708
00:29:43,314 --> 00:29:45,250
Don't forget that you can use UNICHEF.

709
00:29:46,084 --> 00:29:48,086
What? This isn't it.

710
00:29:48,153 --> 00:29:51,055
-It's not working.
-You can use UNICHEF now.

711
00:29:51,122 --> 00:29:52,724
-Here.
